    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"thumbs up\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f44d\" role=\"img\" title=\"thumbs up\">:thumbs_up:</span> dicej submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13812#pullrequestreview-4637298213\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 608484015,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783353365
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> dicej created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13812#discussion_r3530050694\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I'm a bit surprised to see <code>warn</code>-level logging in a <code>From</code> implementation.  What's the rationale?</p>\n<p>(same comment applies to <code>p3/conv.rs</code>)</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 608484016,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783353365
    },
    {
        "content": "<p>alexcrichton updated <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13812\">PR #13812</a>.</p>",
        "id": 608489300,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783354969
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> alexcrichton submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13812#pullrequestreview-4637798085\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 608490093,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783355199
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> alexcrichton created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13812#discussion_r3530466663\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>This is pseudo-preserving preexisting behavior where this is a copy of <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/blob/e7fa0097f924c06a209ea99c980ab84db6128004/crates/wasi-http/src/p2/error.rs#L161-L172\">this function</a> for example, although it wasn't modeled as <code>From</code> before.</p>\n<p>IIRC though the source of this is me asking to add a log here. I'm personally paranoid about dropping error context on the floor as it can create pretty confusing situations downstream, and this was intended to strike a balance of \"someone can figure things out if things go wrong\" with the representation needs here.</p>\n<p>I do agree though it's a bit different being in <code>From</code> vs a freestanding function. Do you have a preference to model this not as <code>From</code> but with an explicit conversion?</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 608490094,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783355199
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> dicej submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13812#pullrequestreview-4638293010\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 608502978,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783359294
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"speech balloon\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4ac\" role=\"img\" title=\"speech balloon\">:speech_balloon:</span> dicej created <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13812#discussion_r3530904779\">PR review comment</a>:</p>\n<blockquote>\n<p>I don't feel strongly about it, although making it an explicit conversion seems reasonable; most people aren't expecting <code>From</code>/<code>Into</code> to have side effects like logging.</p>\n</blockquote>",
        "id": 608502979,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
        "timestamp": 1783359294
    },
    {
        "content": "<p><span aria-label=\"memo\" class=\"emoji emoji-1f4dd\" role=\"img\" title=\"memo\">:memo:</span> dicej submitted <a href=\"https://github.com/bytecodealliance/wasmtime/pull/13812#pullrequestreview-4638332374\">PR review</a>.</p>",
        "id": 608504219,
        "sender_full_name": "Wasmtime GitHub notifications bot",
